A man has been killed at a bus stop outside one of the busiest rail stations in Britain in the early hours of this morning.

Police were called to a stop near London's Waterloo station at 2.45am  where officers found a man in his forties with serious head injuries.

Crews had received reports a man had been attacked but when the London Ambulance Service arrived at the scene he was pronounced dead.

